  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-04-10",
    "date": "2019-07-08T18:44:37Z",
    "text": "Jonny Wade Pediatric Cancer Research Act\n\nThis bill terminates (1) the taxpayer election to designate $3 of income tax liability for financing of presidential election campaigns, (2) the Presidential Election Campaign Fund, and (3) the Presidential Primary Matching Payment Account.\n\nThe Department of the Treasury must transfer the funds remaining in the Presidential Election Campaign Fund to the 10-Year Pediatric Research Initiative Fund.\n\nThe National Institutes of Health (NIH) must prioritize certain pediatric research that does not replicate existing NIH research activities."
  },
